<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-001 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  3 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijani Foreign Minister Concludes Visit, Departs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA3012154493 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1525 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> TA3012154493 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Dec 30 (AA) -- Azerbaijani Foreign Minister 
Gasan Gasanov said on Thursday [30 December] that no one could 
spoil friendship ties between Turkish Republics. 
  Gasanov departed Turkey after completing his official 
contacts. 
  Foreign Ministry officials commenting on the visit said 
Turkey and Azerbaijan decided that Nakhichevan Autonomous 
Republic's border could not be changed by force. 
  It went on saying that the two countries decided to set up a 
study group to prepare a new protocol about a joint border 
between these two countries. 
  Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin said Turkey will extend 
Azerbaijan $10 million credit within the framework of a protocol 
which was earlier signed between the foreign ministries of 
Turkey and Azerbaijan. 
  The credit will be used in the construction of diplomatic 
buildings that are to be set up in Baku. 
  President Suleyman Demirel invited Azeri President Geydar 
Aliyev to Turkey and Gasanov said the visit will probably take 
place in Jan. 
  Gasanov said a summit meeting of Turkish Republics which 
will 
be held between Jan 21 and 22 in Baku will show the other 
countries that no one will be able to spoil our friendship ties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-57814 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu002aa_94001" </HT>


