<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Would Consider Visa </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401134094 Berlin N-TV in German 1100 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0401134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin N-TV </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel has spoken out in 
favor of a political dialogue with the Russian nationalist 
leader Zhirinovskiy. In an N-TV interview, Kinkel explained the 
conditions that might lead to an entry visa being issued for the 
right-wing extremist: 
  [Begin Kinkel recording] I would not be worried about 
getting 
involved in a discussion with him, not be concerned that we 
could not be a match for him and for his extremist theories and 
arguments. I did not say, however, that I was prepared to invite 
him to Germany tomorrow for a discussion or to take part in a 
discussion. However, if he does get invited, for example, to 
take part in a specific discussion by a political foundation or 
is invited by someone here in Germany at some point, if we have 
the opportunity to tell him quite clearly what we think of his 
theories, and if the right people would debate him, then I would 
say we could and should think about it at least. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

