<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNFICYP Spokesman Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0401081094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 0530 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0401081094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Turkish side made new allegations yesterday by 
claiming that there were incidents on the confrontation line. 
In an Istanbul dispatch, ANATOLIA News Agency reported that the 
Rauf Denktas regime reported to the UN Forces in Cyprus 
[UNFICYP] that the Turkish positions were fired upon by Greek 
Cypriots. According to the news agency, the so-called incident 
took place at noon yesterday. 
  A UNFICYP spokesman to CyBC [Cyprus Broadcasting 
Corporation] 
said last night that he has no information about the Turkish 
allegations. At the same time, the National Guard General Staff 
stressed that the Turkish allegations are a new attempt to 
create problems. 

</TEXT>

