<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis Hails Joint Defense Doctrine `Significance' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3112122993 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1000 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> NC3112122993 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis has hailed the new 
Greek-Cypriot defense doctrine's significance, stressing that 
peace in Cyprus will be more secure as Greece becomes more 
involved. The president said the situation would change 
significantly when the invader knows that every new aggressive 
action in Cyprus implies a Greek-Turkish war. 
  Kliridhis said the defense doctrine will be go into effect 
during the visit by Greek Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis and 
a delegation of senior military officials in early January. 
  The president said this to National Guardsmen this morning 
when he visited National Guard posts in Nicosia. Defense 
Minister Kostandinos Iliadhis and National Guard Chief General 
Yeoryios Siradhakis accompanied Kliridhis. 

