<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rexrodt Says Zhirinovskiy No Threat to Economic Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401210294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 2012 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0401210294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Berlin (DDP/ADN) -- In the view of German Economics 
Minister Guenter Rexrodt (Free Democratic Party), the recent 
threats by the Russian nationalist, Zhirinovskiy, do not 
constitute a threat to economic relations between Germany and 
Russia. In an interview with the Berlin-based national 
newspaper DIE WELT (Wednesday [5 January] edition), Rexrodt said 
Russian-German economic relations have "a sound basis" which 
have developed out of "mutual interest." Their strength was 
also proven in the difficult Cold War period. 
  Rexrodt stressed that "Yeltsin and the Russian Government 
continue to consider the further expansion of economic ties with 
the West as their top priority." It is clear to Moscow that the 
industrialized states and the international financial 
institutions play an important part in the reform process. 

</TEXT>

