<H3> <TI>   Unemployment Reaches `New Record High' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401223194 Munich ARD Television Network in German 1900 
GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401223194 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich ARD Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Unemployment in Germany has reached a new record 
high. At the end of December, 3.7 million people in Germany were 
registered unemployed. The new data was presented today by the 
Ursula Engelen-Kefer, deputy chairwoman of the German Trade 
Unions Association [DGB], who is also a member of the Federal 
Labor Office's administrative board. According to these 
figures, the number of unemployed rose in the west by 25 percent 
to 2.5 million over the last year. In the east, 1.175 million 
were registered unemployed. This is an increase of 75,000. The 
official unemployment figures will be published tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

