<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister on UNPROFOR's Problems in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401181594 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1700 
GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401181594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The French foreign minister says he understands the 
anger and revolt of UN Protection Forces [UNPROFOR] commanders 
Cot and Briquemont and thinks that the UN role should be 
redefined. Alain Juppe is interviewed by Michel Barthelemy: 
  [Begin Juppe recording] Our soldiers on the ground are 
carrying out a difficult task with admirable courage. The whole 
question is to define their mission. I think that the 
leadership of UNPROFOR was right to raise a certain number of 
questions. The current situation is intolerable. Recently, the 
European Union gathered all the parties concerned around a table 
in Brussels. We particularly asked them one question: Do you 
agree to observe a truce during Christmas? They all said yes, 
and they all went back on their word. 
  We cannot work for peace with parties to the conflict 
preparing for war. This is not a reason for one to be 
discouraged. France should continue its action as it has been 
doing for several months now. As you remember, the UN secretary 
general thought an extra 7,500 soldiers are necessary in the 
safety zones. Only France strengthened its force last July, 
when it sent more than 1,000 additional troops. Where are the 
others? Where are the missing 6,500? [end recording] 

</TEXT>

