<H3> <TI>   U.S., Russian Ambassadors Comment on Developments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0401132594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1130 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0401132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] U.S. Ambassador Richard Boucher said that the United 
States will intensify its efforts to help achieve a Cyprus 
solution this year. Mr. Boucher made this statement upon his 
arrival, with other members of the diplomatic corps, at the 
Presidential Palace where they were received by President 
Glavkos Kliridhis on the occasion of the New Year. Mr. Boucher 
also said that State Department's Coordinator Robert Lamb will 
visit Cyprus, but the time has not been set. 
  When asked by correspondents if he had any statement to 
make, 
British High Commissioner David Dain confined himself to 
expressing good wishes for the New Year. 
  Russian Ambassador to Cyprus Boris Zenkov expressed the wish 
that 1994 will be the last year of Cyprus' division. Asked 
whether Russia intends to appoint an observer to the Cyprus 
issue, he said that his country will wait until the talks begin 
and then consider how it can offer more help. 

</TEXT>

