<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Transportation Minister Leaves for Kazakhstan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0401082494 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2100 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0401082494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Transportation Minister Mehmet Kostepen left for 
Kazakhstan today on an official visit. In a predeparture 
statement at Ankara's Esenboga Airport, Kostepen said his visit 
to Kazakhstan will be extremely useful in raising the level of 
bilateral relations. 
  The two countries will exchange permits governing passenger 
and cargo transportation between Turkey and Kazakhstan, Kostepen 
explained. He expressed the belief that during his visit, 
concrete moves will be undertaken toward the establishment of a 
joint railroad car factory in Kazakhstan, in line with a 
previous agreement. Kostepen noted that Kazakhstan's request to 
purchase railroad cars, as well as ships for internal sea and 
river transportation, from Turkey will also be discussed during 
his visit. He added that the question of nonstop television 
broadcasts will also be raised. The transportation minister's 
visit to Kazakhstan will last three days. 

</TEXT>

