<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Solana Says Tunisia Visit `Very Useful' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401194194 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1400 GMT 4 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today, Tuesday [4 January], Spanish Foreign Minister 
Javier Solana returned to Madrid following his official visit to 
Tunisia. Solana described the visit as very useful from all 
points of view because it permitted progress to be made in the 
various fields of cooperation. Before concluding his visit, 
Javier Solana was received today by Tunisian President Zine El 
Abidine Ben Ali, with whom he discussed matters such as 
bilateral relations, the situaton in the Maghreb countries, and 
the common desire to proceed toward formulas which would permit 
greater security in the Mediterranean. 
  The Spanish foreign minister said that another component of 
this visit to Tunisia was related to the peace process in the 
Middle East, for which reason he had a meeting with Palestinian 
leader Yasir 'Arafat. 

</TEXT>

