<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Fails To Pay for Medical Treatment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0501135294 Vienna KURIER in German 5 Jan 94 p 15 </F>
<F P=103> AU0501135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna KURIER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "The Russian's Debts"] </F>
  [Text] Wherever Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, the right-wing 
winner of the Russian elections, appears, he is bound to leave 
everybody confused. During his stay in Austria, the Russian 
went to Graz to have his skin and eyes examined at the local 
hospital. After the treatment he casually disappeared -- without 
paying -- it has now been reported. (Initially the doctors kept 
quiet -- out of politeness toward their "prominent" guest?) Now 
the director of the hospital wants to send a bill for the amount 
outstanding to Moscow. 

</TEXT>

