<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Slovak Delegation Begins Official Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0601092894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 0835 GMT 6 Jan 93 </F>

<F P=103> NC0601092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A large delegation from the Republic of Slovakia 
began a two-day official visit to Cyprus today. The delegation 
is headed by Foreign Minister Josef Moravcik. Economics 
Minister Jan Ducky is also a member of the Slovak delegation. 
This is the first visit by a high-ranking Slovak delegation to 
Cyprus since Czechoslovakia was dissolved a year ago. The visit 
is aimed at strengthening bilateral relations between Cyprus and 
Slovakia. The Cypriot side also wants to brief the visiting 
delegation on the latest developments in the Cyprus issue. 
Furthermore, both Cyprus and Slovakia are interested in 
developing close cooperation in the fields of trade and 
cooperation through European international organizations. 

</TEXT>

