<H3> <TI>   Alleged Solingen Arsonists Charged With Murder </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU3012121493 Hamburg DPA in German 1557 GMT 29 Dec 93--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3012121493 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hamburg (DPA) -- According to WESTDEUTSCHE 
ALLGEMEINE ZEITUNG (WAZ, Essen), the Federal Prosecutor's Office 
has brought charges against the alleged attackers of Solingen. 
[On 26th May 1993 two Turkish women and three children died when 
their house was set on fire.] They would be tried for five 
counts of murder and 14 counts of attempted murder. The young 
men are suspected of having set fire to a house occupied by 
Turks accepting that the inhabitants might die as a consequence. 
  According to WAZ, the Federal Prosecutor's Office will hold 
the trial at Duesseldorf Higher Regional Court. Recently there 
had been doubts about whether the four detained suspects were 
guilty. However, following further checks, the Federal Court of 
Justice had upheld the detention order. 
  A spokesman for the Federal Prosecutor's Office would not 
confirm or deny the information. "No comment" was the reply to 
an enquiry in Karlsruhe. Generally officials would comment only 
after the suspects had been informed of the charges. 

</TEXT>

