Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Inflation Confirmed at 4 Percent"] </F>
  [Text] Rome, 30 Dec (ANSA) -- Inflation fell to an annual 
rate of 4 percent in December, ending the year at the lowest 
level since 1969, the national statistics bureau, ISTAT, 
confirmed Thursday [29 December]. 
  ISTAT said preliminary figures taken in eight sample cities 
earlier this month and confirmed today showed consumer prices 
remained stock-still in December, bringing inflation to a 
24-year low. 
  Below is a table showing monthly inflation rates from 1987 
to 
the present: 


