<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   * Communist Chief: Quit EU Accession Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94EN0181C Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT in Finnish 30 Nov 93 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> 94EN0181C </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "SKP(Y)'s Hakanen: We Must Start To </F>
Look for Alternatives to the EU"] 
  [Text] STT--Yrjo Hakanen, chairman of the SKP(Y) [Finnish 
Communist Party (Unity)], wants to end the negotiations on 
membership in the European Union [EU]. At a meeting of his 
party's Central Committee in Helsinki on Saturday [27 November], 
Hakanen said the general validity of collective bargaining 
agreements and the labor union movement's rights to enter into 
international agreements have not been recognized in the 
membership negotiations. There has been too little mention of 
the funding of social security and public services. 
  In Hakanen's opinion, a radical shift to the right and the 
West has occurred in Finland's foreign and security policies. 
Whereas an independent neutrality policy used to be emphasized, 
now submission to the EU foreign and security policies is the 
point of departure. 

</TEXT>

