<H3> <TI>   Comments on Withdrawing UN Troops </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0601142294 Brussels BELGA in French 1921 GMT 5 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0601142294 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels BELGA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed GGD (SVD): "Mr. Delcroix Speaks of </F>
Withdrawing Blue Helmets"; as released by Brussels BELGA 
Database] 
  [Text] Brussels, 5 Jan 94 (BELGA) -- Belgian Defense 
Minister Leo Delcroix threatened on Wednesday [5 January] to 
withdraw the Belgian Blue Helmets from Bosnia-Herzegovina, where 
they are 300 of the 12,000 soldiers in the UN Protection Force 
(UNPROFOR) in this former Yugoslav republic. 
  France, Spain, Great Britain, and Canada, the principal 
suppliers of men to Bosnia, have begun to reexamine the mission 
of their Blue Helmets. Lord David Owen, the European mediator 
for the former Yugoslavia, believes the UN forces may withdraw 
next spring if no apparent progress is made in the peace talks 
within the next two months. 
  Interviewed on Wednesday evening by RTBF [French-language 
Belgian broadcast media] Television, Mr. Delcroix also spoke of 
the possibility of withdrawing Belgian forces from Bosnia in the 
absence of a "political solution" to the civil war between the 
Serbs, Croats, and Muslims. "We must wait until the end of the 
winter," the defense minister added. In March or April, we will 
have to "think of new means (of continuing the UNPROFOR mission) 
or withdraw," he stated. 

</TEXT>

