<H3> <TI>   East, West German Railway Companies Unite </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0101141294 Hamburg DPA in German 1331 GMT 1 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0101141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Frankfurt/Main (DPA) -- The Deutsche Bahn AG [German 
railway company] was established in Frankfurt today. Company 
Director Hanz Duerr and board member Diethelm Vack, as well as a 
representative of the German Government signed the foundation 
document at a lawyer's office in Frankfurt. 
  The public limited company is owned outright by the German 
Government and will replace the Bundesbahn [in the west] and the 
Reichsbahn [in the east], which thereby cease to exist after 
operating for 44 and 56 years respectively. Under the 
agreement, the railway company will also transfer existing debts 
of 70 million German marks, which will now be assumed by the 
German Government. 

</TEXT>

