<H3> <TI>   Government Appeals to Iran To Pardon Engineer </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501125394 Hamburg DPA in German 1156 GMT 5 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0501125394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Bonn/Tehran (DPA)--German Foreign Ministry 
spokesman Martin Erdmann said today that the German Government, 
which formally appealed for a pardon immediately after the 
Iranian death sentence against the German engineer Helmut 
Szimkus was confirmed, is still hoping for his release. [passage 
omitted] 
  Intensive and close contacts are apparently being used 
between Bonn and Tehran to stop the death sentence from being 
carried out. This does not appear impossible, according to 
informed sources. The German Foreign Ministry merely confirmed 
that the formal petition for pardon had only been possible once 
the long legal procedure ended with the Supreme Court rejecting 
the appeal. 

</TEXT>

